<subSubSection id="147735B973A9C270ADCE1B798D841960" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="2577D8A86379F5207B19B8AF0203FFBE" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4B67269E4545436995FEE371B386B6E1" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Head dark brown. Antennae yellowish except F3, F4 brownish, club brownish except yellowish apex. Mesosoma yellow except propodeum brown. Midlobe of mesoscutum with two pairs of long setae. Scutellum with a longitudinal depression in anterior 2/3.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0AAB3156AFC553ED26CB09F685054FEA" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" type="description">
<paragraph id="33A90CC7019A16DE8DB17CE279A41BBB" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="48444DB0E12897F72CC51FCCD57E90A5" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis id="8C00FCFE7ADB3AAF50EC40DCE2366AA6" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Female.</emphasis>
Body length 2.4 mm, fore wing length 1.7 mm. Head dark brown. Antennae yellowish with F3 and F4 brownish, club brownish except yellowish apex. Mesoscutum, axillae and scutellum yellow. Propodeum brown. Legs yellowish. Gaster mostly yellow with two brown transverse bands posteriorly and margins brown. Ovipositor black.
</paragraph>
<caption id="B8EFF5C23DDA214E8B0F5B8D6A3F752F" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.80671.figures1-4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671711" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" start="Figures 1–4" startId="F1">
<paragraph id="11D423E49DAB99247AC8DF0562481B40" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis id="2FEE66321666977F9FF4B0E74B4CFF90" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Figures 1-4.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="F9EDC1CB218A8F1FE4BCA2E3C79D3474" class="Insecta" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. depressa" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="depressa">
<emphasis id="C448AAD81994D845C374CE0E76EE8340" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">D. depressa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., female, holotype 
<emphasis id="42F76EAC8F0434B96D6708D52E7F7E30" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">1</emphasis>
habitus in dorsal view 
<emphasis id="B4734CB87CD7400BD203EC08A859CA92" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">2</emphasis>
head in frontal view 
<emphasis id="DF9B5709F909DCD561C92D35AD63D175" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">3</emphasis>
fore wing 
<emphasis id="AB6B0D627FEC68D9AF1CDC6BDC50572D" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">4</emphasis>
hind wing. Scale bars: 100 
<normalizedToken id="9D06F17BBB5F8CDED001CE141C1E380A" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="E1E373E7F350683EC49523C11D912391" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis id="37A9230516B0BBD941A9E2D710108D0D" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Head</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="FFD276CB2232EC377DC32F87963A9092" captionStart="Figures 1–4" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 4. D. depressa sp. nov., female, holotype 1 habitus in dorsal view 2 head in frontal view 3 fore wing 4 hind wing. Scale bars: 100 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.80671.figures1-4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671711" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">2</figureCitation>
) 1.2
<normalizedToken id="CA49AC14BCEE8916600070C1C0A82B3E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as wide as high in frontal view and ~ 2.2
<normalizedToken id="95624B9D9914B7619E52AD8F5CD8E253" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as wide as long in dorsal view. Lower face smooth, frons weakly reticulate. Vertex with engraved reticulation, meshes isodiametric, and scattered setae. POL 1.8
<normalizedToken id="F398D130F49E94247C6AB5648EE78F71" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
OOL. Malar space 0.4
<normalizedToken id="8CADD6CEAFBB7431EFAD0F0FFEF70B16" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
eye height. Occiput weakly reticulate. Relative measurements (length: width): scape = 28: 5; pedicel = 10: 5; F1 = 16: 5; F2 = 11: 5; F3 = 12: 7; F4 = 10: 7; clava = 16: 7.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5FFEF1C107FBB613ECEFF89F8A9BBE22" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis id="56D81FD4C2ED86E99EC8495688C61B02" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Mesosoma</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6AC39957062DACB6480DCD7C1C45C7F8" captionStart="Figures 1–4" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 4. D. depressa sp. nov., female, holotype 1 habitus in dorsal view 2 head in frontal view 3 fore wing 4 hind wing. Scale bars: 100 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.80671.figures1-4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671711" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">1</figureCitation>
). Midlobe of mesoscutum punctate with two pairs of long setae, lateral lobe of mesoscutum reticulate. Notauli ending laterad to inner angles of axilla. Axillae weakly reticulate and separated from each other. Scutellum with a longitudinal depression in anterior 2/3 and two pairs of long setae, sublateral grooves meet posteriorly. Spiracle with a transverse carina anteriorly, separated from metanotum by a distance shorter than a diameter of spiracle; each propodeal callus with seven long setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E45CBF1307B8B4EE29A7BFF7A8CE204F" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis id="E3901026FA37A5B773F1E7EB8221DF8A" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis id="D7A091AC2913CF7D661663C86B65DCA7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Wings</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Fore wing (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="433C4473623E934B9258D13522E8321F" captionStart="Figures 1–4" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 4. D. depressa sp. nov., female, holotype 1 habitus in dorsal view 2 head in frontal view 3 fore wing 4 hind wing. Scale bars: 100 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.80671.figures1-4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671711" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">3</figureCitation>
) 2.3
<normalizedToken id="9A5D631C6E8C4028499621CAF4DCD460" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide. Speculum narrow. Relative measurements (length): SMV = 43; MV = 40; PMV = 22; STV = 16. Hind wing (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2A32DB35C73DF46487560D80B40BF63C" captionStart="Figures 1–4" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 4. D. depressa sp. nov., female, holotype 1 habitus in dorsal view 2 head in frontal view 3 fore wing 4 hind wing. Scale bars: 100 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.80671.figures1-4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671711" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">4</figureCitation>
) ~ 4.0
<normalizedToken id="FE9901E76F9A19EB609049781CF27C79" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="97EFBCF98312C57E7787DF133999DAFF" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis id="663056B2132ABB3EF85562B24DB7AFCF" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Metasoma</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D5DA6BD2A7179F573F1A919DEDD7E4D2" captionStart="Figures 1–4" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 4. D. depressa sp. nov., female, holotype 1 habitus in dorsal view 2 head in frontal view 3 fore wing 4 hind wing. Scale bars: 100 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.80671.figures1-4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671711" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">1</figureCitation>
). Gaster ovate, 1.8
<normalizedToken id="CB13D6C9C37DD1FCAA44E5B4325D97A1" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide, and 1.1
<normalizedToken id="82DAF082514926071A1D39D2E17A55AC" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as mesosoma. Ovipositor exserted beyond apex of gaster.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="49DE0A600BF701E971275E1DA3ADD947" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis id="2174DC3E4684679798FB0CF76D86449B" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Male.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="55C3902D46B7AA93434768FEC112B45E" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" type="host">
<paragraph id="72D4AFC7D6789B5D52BA1FD8FB46F5C2" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Host.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E755AB9D3661C7BB78043EE6D6149521" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CF8FBC65270429519D8186B26E3D16B8" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="9B110F969F18CAB5DC2CD6F48CD1BC03" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9ACA66FE670CA52AE1C87A5C23F5D094" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">China (Sichuan, Liaoning).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BB9DEC3992E054740A4F069072EF4869" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="6FB07A175B52C167D11BDA3811A4F10E" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0EEE075527AB8F1CA85AFFF038029617" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">
Latin: 
<emphasis id="C58F2F42B1C9E9FCB7C36269F1F640B2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">depressum</emphasis>
= depression, sink; and refers to the longitudinal depression in anterior 2/3 of scutellum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7D940E230E2D53057D94CB3E94FA2967" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="0E90C8740A2824F3CF591B19B8550A48" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="65291D64C272DC3C4200874825903F22" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">This new species differs from all other known members of the genus in having a scutellum with a longitudinal depression on its anterior 2/3.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
